The paper focuses on improving the performance of state-of-the-art vision systems using general-purpose ontologies, specifically MIT's ConceptNet ontology. This involves incorporating knowledge from ConceptNet into a large pool of object detectors derived from deep learning techniques to improve sentence-based image retrieval. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
